commit.message: Update README.md
Should I throw an exception?
Change constants to static as they are file-local.
Rename the UPPER_CASE constants in main.cpp.
A lot more refactoring of braincurses.cpp.
Move atexit handler to main.cpp; add SIGINT handler.
Update includes with new file names.
Update Makefile with new file names.
Move windows.{h,cpp} to braincurses.{h,cpp}.
Rename braincurses.cpp to main.cpp.

Move ncurses code into new Braincurses class.

This is the beginning of a larger refactor of the code in windows.h,
windows.cpp, and braincurses.cpp. I'm generally following the style of
Google's C++ style guide rather than the one I used originally for this
code more than ten years ago.

Refactor braincurses.cpp to use constants.

Use constants for code length and guesses arguments. Also, move argument
parsing and setting to a separate function.
Ignore braincurses binary

Remove SetLength and other unused code.

There is no need for SetLength so it is removed. I also removed some
commented out code from previous debugging sessions. Lastly, I removed
the old IsCorrect method that used vectors.
Add table-based tests for code class.
Use new IsCorrect method.
Updated external/json.
Added new generic IsCorrect.
Add extra whitespace before colons.
Update submodules

Trying out bandit.

After finding liblittletest wasn't going to work for my table-driven
tests I am going to try something newer. It seems like BDD-style test
frameworks are hot so lets give this a try. I am calling it quits for
the night without getting to actually implementing the full table test
(assuming it is feasible to do so with this framework.)
Add bandit test framework as submodule.
Add YCM files to .gitignore.
Remove littletest.cpp and update Makefile.
Remove code_test.cpp.

Refactor Code class.

Cleaned up the API of Code and applied the changes through the code. I
will remove code_test.cpp as the liblittletest framework isn't going to
cut it for the testing I want to do.
Update README.md about terminal color issues.
Add a few comments. Change single-line if style.
Remove 'how to apply' section of LICENSE.
Remove unused includes.
